-------------------------------------------------------------------

If you use Norton Utilities 6.0 - be careful !!!
------------------------------------------------
See PC WEEK July 29, 1991, Vol. 8 No. 30 !
------------------------------------------
In brief :
------------------------------------*------------------------------
     operation			    | result
------------------------------------*------------------------------
Using Norton Speed Disk with the    | Computer freezes; FAT and
DOS 5.0 FastOpen caching directory  | boot sectors on hard disk
utility 			    | destroyed
------------------------------------*------------------------------
Running Norton Cache with	    | Computer freezes; corrupts
Desqview, QEMM or Windows	    | Windows files; fatal error
				    | message
------------------------------------*------------------------------
Marking files in Erase Protect that | Computer freezes
should be moved to a less-used part |
of the hard disk when deleted	    |
------------------------------------*------------------------------
Searching directories that have no  | Error message: can't find
subdirectory using the *.* command  | directory in *.*
in Text Search			    |
------------------------------------*------------------------------
Copying files to or from	    | Operation is aborted, system
low-density 5.25-inch disks when    | reboots
Norton Cache is installed	    |
------------------------------------*------------------------------
For more information see PC WEEK July 29, 1991, page 8
(article "Glitches in Norton Utilities 6.0 Prompt Update from Symantec")
